cs.DB, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DB (Database): The paper focuses on managing IoT data, which is typically large in scale and volume, and requires efficient storage and processing techniques. This aligns with the scope of the Database sub-category.
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the Internet of Things (IoT) approach, which involves connecting everyday objects to the Internet and facilitating machine-to-human and machine-to-machine communication. This aligns with the scope of the Networking and Internet Architecture sub-category.
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses techniques for processing and storing IoT data, which often requires distributed and parallel computing approaches. This aligns with the scope of the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing sub-category.
4. cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the challenges of developing applications and services for IoT, which requires software engineering techniques for managing complexity and ensuring reliability. This aligns with the scope of the Software Engineering sub-category.
5. cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper briefly touches upon the societal implications of IoT, such as privacy and security concerns. This aligns with the scope of the Computers and Society sub-category.
